WEBVTT

00:14.015 --> 00:16.682
        [waves crashing]

00:33.234 --> 00:36.101
        [dramatic music]

03:18.933 --> 03:20.832
       Well, are you just
     going to stand there?

03:22.636 --> 03:23.635
      That depends on you.

03:24.438 --> 03:25.470
   Really? I don't think so.

03:26.707 --> 03:27.639
            Kiss me.

03:28.976 --> 03:30.642
       If you let me in.

03:33.948 --> 03:36.481
       -[woman laughing]
         -[man shushes]

03:36.684 --> 03:38.283
       You are the worst.

03:38.285 --> 03:39.218
            You are.

03:55.436 --> 03:57.736
     Oh, not on your life.

03:57.738 --> 03:59.605
     Oh, come on, you might
     like it if you try it.

04:00.474 --> 04:01.840
         [man coughing]

04:03.978 --> 04:04.943
        How's he doing?

04:07.281 --> 04:08.447
 I don't want to talk about it.

04:08.449 --> 04:10.515
         [man coughing]

04:10.517 --> 04:11.617
          [man] <i> Roger!</i>

04:13.254 --> 04:14.653
         Where's Roger?

04:14.655 --> 04:15.821
         [Roger sighs]

04:18.826 --> 04:19.925
           [knocking]

04:19.927 --> 04:21.892
        -[woman] Roger.
             -Yep?

04:22.496 --> 04:24.029
            [woman]
 He won't be awake much longer.

04:24.031 --> 04:25.764
  I need to give him his meds.

04:25.766 --> 04:26.898
            One sec.

04:27.768 --> 04:28.767
           Go ahead.

04:35.776 --> 04:37.943
         [man coughing]

04:45.352 --> 04:47.753
        -[gentle music]
       -[birds chirping]

05:42.910 --> 05:43.775
    [Daphne] That feel good?

05:43.777 --> 05:46.111
         Mm, wonderful.

05:48.115 --> 05:49.114
        Thank you, baby.

05:56.123 --> 05:57.923
      All right, let's do
    your legs and feet next.

05:59.493 --> 06:00.726
     Can't say no to that.

06:22.116 --> 06:23.582
 Tell me about your day, baby.

06:28.389 --> 06:29.572
    There's nothing special.

06:29.573 --> 06:30.756
       Just dealing with
     these two fancy mama's

06:30.758 --> 06:33.058
  and their two fancy babies.

06:34.895 --> 06:36.161
        Sounds familiar.

06:44.438 --> 06:47.739
        Did another bill
     from Wells Fargo come?

06:57.918 --> 06:59.084
        I didn't see it.

07:01.455 --> 07:02.654
         Are you sure?

07:08.095 --> 07:09.861
    What are you going to do
    about it if it did come?

07:11.131 --> 07:12.564
  How are you going to pay it?

07:13.434 --> 07:14.900
     I get paid next week.

07:15.903 --> 07:18.136
 Your $12 an hour won't cut it.

07:19.139 --> 07:20.138
        It'll help, Ma.

07:22.209 --> 07:23.141
          Did it come?

07:27.481 --> 07:28.480
          Did it come?

07:35.789 --> 07:37.889
 We are not losing this house.

07:39.960 --> 07:40.892
              Ma.

07:42.996 --> 07:45.831
      If I didn't see it,
        it didn't come.

07:48.135 --> 07:49.067
             Fine.

07:52.072 --> 07:53.772
       I'm having a drink
       with Twyla later.

07:53.774 --> 07:55.207
       I'll probably just
      crash at her place.

07:56.944 --> 07:58.109
      That girl from work?

07:59.513 --> 08:01.079
         She must have
      a really nice place.

08:01.081 --> 08:02.881
  It's just easier and closer.

08:03.650 --> 08:04.716
  She lives on the west side.

08:04.718 --> 08:08.220
You sure you don't have someone
  you're not telling me about?

08:09.690 --> 08:10.689
             Ma...

08:11.658 --> 08:12.624
             Stop.

08:13.961 --> 08:14.893
             Okay.

08:16.864 --> 08:17.829
             Okay.

08:20.601 --> 08:22.767
      [soft ambient music]

09:16.924 --> 09:18.056
        Rog, let me in.

09:20.727 --> 09:21.893
        Roger, come on.

09:26.133 --> 09:27.832
      Baby, what's wrong?

09:32.773 --> 09:33.705
            My dad.

09:50.023 --> 09:51.122
           Fuck him.

09:54.728 --> 09:55.794
           Fuck him.

10:03.770 --> 10:05.003
         [Roger sighs]

10:16.350 --> 10:17.749
           I'm sorry.

10:20.887 --> 10:22.687
        [birds chirping]

10:23.857 --> 10:25.657
        [phone buzzing]

10:34.301 --> 10:35.634
           Oh, shit.

10:39.006 --> 10:40.639
             Babe.

10:40.641 --> 10:42.741
         -I got to go.
          -[he groans]

10:42.743 --> 10:43.675
           I'm sorry.

10:45.078 --> 10:46.344
       Will you be okay?

11:08.335 --> 11:10.035
         You can go out
      the front door now.

11:12.939 --> 11:13.872
         Are you sure?

11:17.344 --> 11:18.276
          We're free.

11:22.749 --> 11:23.815
       I'll be back soon.

11:37.831 --> 11:39.764
         -[door thuds]
       -[birds chirping]

12:04.257 --> 12:05.190
              Hey.

12:05.826 --> 12:06.825
              Hi.

12:07.427 --> 12:08.359
           Hey, you.

12:09.796 --> 12:11.329
Are you sure you want me there?

12:14.234 --> 12:16.501
      Yes, of course I do.

12:17.437 --> 12:18.470
        Hey, I need you.

12:19.239 --> 12:20.171
            Please?

12:21.241 --> 12:22.440
             Okay.

12:26.279 --> 12:27.345
           After you.

12:33.854 --> 12:34.853
         [phone rings]

12:42.062 --> 12:43.995
      This is a sensitive
         family matter.

12:43.997 --> 12:45.997
        Roger, we should
   probably speak privately.

12:45.999 --> 12:48.366
          Yeah, well,
    Daphne is my family now.

12:49.236 --> 12:50.435
         Good morning.

12:51.104 --> 12:52.203
         [door closes]

12:55.342 --> 12:56.407
        Daphne, welcome.

12:56.409 --> 12:59.177
      -Have a seat, Roger.
     -I'm good right here.

12:59.980 --> 13:01.513
   Your father was concerned

13:02.315 --> 13:04.315
    that you are not living
     up to your potential.

13:04.317 --> 13:05.550
    Cut the bullshit, Zorn.

13:07.220 --> 13:08.553
          Your father
   left you the beach house.

13:09.122 --> 13:10.221
              And?

13:10.223 --> 13:14.793
      And it's a property
     of significant value.

13:15.328 --> 13:17.896
  He set up a trust that would
   pay for all of its upkeep,

13:17.898 --> 13:20.231
       taxes, everything
       is taken care of.

13:20.233 --> 13:22.500
  Big fuckin' deal. Why don't
  you tell me about the money.

13:23.036 --> 13:25.336
        The 15 mil or so
      that should be mine.

13:25.338 --> 13:26.938
       You father thought
     that you would benefit

13:26.940 --> 13:28.540
         from learning
    how to support yourself.

13:28.542 --> 13:31.042
 -What the fuck does that mean?
        -Roger, please.

13:33.446 --> 13:35.013
      It means bar-tending
      while you're waiting

13:35.015 --> 13:37.415
      for you inheritance
        is not a career.

13:37.417 --> 13:38.416
 What about the Portland house?

13:43.023 --> 13:44.289
  He left you the beach house.

13:44.291 --> 13:46.057
        [keys jingling]

13:49.563 --> 13:51.396
  The remainder of his assets
     are going to be set up

13:51.398 --> 13:53.932
      into a trust for any
    heirs that you may have.

13:55.836 --> 13:58.303
        -Your children.
 -Yeah, I know what heirs are.

13:58.305 --> 14:00.004
   If and when you have any,

14:00.006 --> 14:03.107
      they'll inherit 100%
     of the trust's assets.

14:03.977 --> 14:05.543
 And what if there are no kids?

14:06.346 --> 14:08.479
          -What then?
        -Then the money
       will be divided up

14:08.481 --> 14:10.381
 into charities of his choice.

14:10.383 --> 14:11.916
     And you're the asshole
         who determines

14:11.918 --> 14:13.051
   what those charities are.

14:13.453 --> 14:15.620
    -How fuckin' convenient.
         -Roger, stop.

14:16.323 --> 14:19.357
 Roger, I have always followed
    my clients instructions

14:19.359 --> 14:21.626
    whether if I agreed with
   their assessments or not.

14:21.628 --> 14:24.162
Did you follow his instructions
   when you were fucking him?

14:24.164 --> 14:25.496
            -Roger.
              -No!

14:26.132 --> 14:27.599
          [door shuts]

14:30.937 --> 14:32.237
     Like father like son.

14:33.206 --> 14:35.106
    No, Roger is different.

14:36.409 --> 14:39.510
       Honestly, Daphne.
 I'm surprised to see you here.

14:40.280 --> 14:41.579
      I strongly urge you

14:42.449 --> 14:44.048
to reconsider your involvement.

14:46.319 --> 14:49.487
       You may find this
      hard to believe but

14:50.423 --> 14:51.556
       we love each other

14:52.392 --> 14:53.558
           very much.

14:54.327 --> 14:55.927
   Then best of luck to you.

15:10.944 --> 15:12.143
             Baby!

15:13.013 --> 15:14.579
      -Baby, are you okay?
         -That bastard,

15:14.581 --> 15:16.347
      he's just doing this
    because we're together.

15:17.484 --> 15:19.284
     It's okay, it's over.

15:19.286 --> 15:20.551
          -He's gone.
          -No, no, no.

15:21.388 --> 15:23.087
     No, listen, maybe his
    passive aggressive shit

15:23.089 --> 15:24.422
     is the best thing that
      ever happened to us.

15:27.160 --> 15:29.160
    Ever since you came back
          into my life

15:29.162 --> 15:30.628
    I knew we were meant for
   each other so let's do it.

15:30.630 --> 15:32.297
       Let's get married,
        let's have kids.

15:34.668 --> 15:36.167
   Daph, you love me, right?

15:36.169 --> 15:40.705
  We get the fuck out of town,
      we go to the beach,
we live our lives how we want to

15:40.707 --> 15:43.007
   and we tell everyone else
      who thinks they know

15:43.009 --> 15:45.476
       what's best for us
       to fuck off, hmm?

15:47.213 --> 15:48.513
             -When?
             -Now.

15:50.283 --> 15:52.450
 Tomorrow, tomorrow, next week,
     whenever you're ready.

15:52.452 --> 15:54.085
       But I have a job.

15:54.087 --> 15:58.957
    -I can't just walk out.
  -Two years and you're still
    assistant floor manager,

15:58.959 --> 16:00.024
    you're better than that.

16:03.363 --> 16:05.296
        Hey, I want you,

16:06.199 --> 16:07.265
          I want this.

16:08.168 --> 16:09.367
    Let's make it official.

16:12.706 --> 16:13.738
         Is that a yes?

16:15.709 --> 16:17.642
             -Yes.
       -I can't hear you.

16:18.545 --> 16:20.078
         -I said, yes.
             -Yes?

16:20.080 --> 16:21.579
             -Yes.
        -Is that a yes?

16:21.581 --> 16:23.481
     -A yes? Is that a yes?
             -Yes!

16:23.483 --> 16:24.716
           [laughing]

16:25.685 --> 16:27.719
       [liquid splashing]

16:27.721 --> 16:29.687
         [somber music]

16:47.474 --> 16:49.173
       [pills clattering]

16:51.511 --> 16:53.544
        [Ma] Do you want
     anything else to eat?

16:56.049 --> 16:58.349
       No, Ma. I'm fine.

16:59.719 --> 17:01.586
       [toilet flushing]

17:09.362 --> 17:10.294
         [Ma] For what?

17:11.397 --> 17:14.065
   It's for work, I told you,
        it's a retreat.

17:14.701 --> 17:16.267
    My daughter, look at me.

17:16.803 --> 17:19.037
    I wasn't born yesterday,
           you know.

17:24.277 --> 17:26.109
       I put some dinners
     in the fridge for you

17:27.113 --> 17:28.713
    and if you need anything
         just call me.

17:30.383 --> 17:31.716
          Look at me.

17:35.555 --> 17:36.687
      Don't you trust me?

17:37.757 --> 17:39.223
         Of course, Ma.

17:41.528 --> 17:43.094
I don't want you getting hurt...

17:43.096 --> 17:44.228
            I am 24.

17:45.365 --> 17:47.365
    I'm not a child anymore.

17:47.367 --> 17:49.200
  ...or doing anything stupid.

17:52.772 --> 17:54.405
 I put some money on the mantle

17:55.341 --> 17:57.208
   and if Wells Fargo calls,

17:58.344 --> 18:00.144
         just tell 'em
    the checks in the mail.

18:07.387 --> 18:09.420
   [melancholic piano music]

19:32.772 --> 19:35.173
           -You okay?
       -Yeah, yeah, uh...

19:35.175 --> 19:36.941
    Why don't you go on in?

19:36.943 --> 19:38.509
      I'll be in in a sec.

19:38.511 --> 19:39.710
           -You sure?
             -Yeah,

19:40.813 --> 19:41.913
             yeah.

19:47.353 --> 19:48.419
         [Roger sighs]

19:48.855 --> 19:50.454
        [waves crashing]

20:03.536 --> 20:04.802
          [door bangs]

20:13.880 --> 20:15.213
             Roger!

20:18.685 --> 20:21.419
      [soft ambient music]

20:41.674 --> 20:43.608
         [eerie music]

20:44.477 --> 20:45.543
             Roger!

21:31.791 --> 21:33.758
     Lookin' for something?

21:37.730 --> 21:39.864
         It used to be
   my favorite thinkin' spot.

21:41.401 --> 21:42.500
      Want to come inside?

21:45.338 --> 21:46.904
       What, you scared?

21:46.906 --> 21:47.872
              No.

21:52.545 --> 21:53.911
        [both laughing]

21:56.082 --> 21:57.481
          [Roger] Woo.

21:59.052 --> 22:00.951
        [both laughing]

22:03.656 --> 22:05.423
     Did Zorn really sleep
         with your dad?

22:07.727 --> 22:08.659
              Why?

22:08.661 --> 22:11.862
          Well, that's
      seriously unethical.

22:13.366 --> 22:15.566
    I don't really remember
      much from back then.

22:16.002 --> 22:19.804
 After my mom died I was pretty
    wasted most of the time.

22:22.508 --> 22:24.842
      So, maybe you should
       contest the will.

22:27.914 --> 22:28.879
          Yeah, maybe.

22:31.684 --> 22:33.551
          I'd see Zorn
   in the morning sometimes.

22:35.088 --> 22:36.120
          So, she was?

22:36.956 --> 22:38.389
  He never admitted it though.

22:40.426 --> 22:42.660
   Like I said, I was pretty
    on fleek with the drugs
       at that point so--

22:42.662 --> 22:44.362
         Oh, no. stop.

22:44.864 --> 22:46.464
[southern accent] That's wrong.

22:46.466 --> 22:47.398
             What?

22:48.935 --> 22:50.568
That's just not how you say it.

22:51.070 --> 22:52.737
           On fleek?
    Well, how do you say it?

22:54.040 --> 22:57.141
   Well, you don't use it to
describe how fucked up you are.

22:57.143 --> 23:00.077
         Well... were.

23:00.079 --> 23:02.480
  -Then tell me how to use it.
              -No.

23:03.449 --> 23:05.015
       It's not happening
         you just stick

23:05.017 --> 23:06.917
 to your stoner white boy talk.

23:07.787 --> 23:09.453
 Talk like a stoner white boy?

23:09.455 --> 23:10.888
     [laughs] Yeah, you do.

23:11.958 --> 23:15.893
         You talk like
    a rich stoner white boy.

23:15.895 --> 23:17.428
    Well, is that a problem?

23:19.065 --> 23:19.997
              No.

23:26.072 --> 23:27.905
 Your dad come here much alone?

23:29.475 --> 23:30.608
       I don't know, why?

23:30.610 --> 23:34.512
 It doesn't seem like anyone's
   been here for a long time.

23:37.817 --> 23:38.749
          He was sick.

23:40.019 --> 23:41.419
      Well, yeah, I know.

23:42.588 --> 23:43.687
        I just meant...

23:44.757 --> 23:45.823
           around...

23:46.426 --> 23:47.425
         on the beach.

23:52.031 --> 23:53.164
              Rog.

23:56.669 --> 23:57.601
             Um...

24:01.107 --> 24:02.873
       You know, my mom's
    father built this house.

24:04.911 --> 24:05.910
       She loved it here.

24:08.781 --> 24:10.047
   And he couldn't stand it.

24:11.884 --> 24:13.851
        So, he made sure
  I couldn't stand it either.

24:17.223 --> 24:18.722
   And then he gave it to me.

24:19.659 --> 24:20.925
           [chuckles]

24:23.563 --> 24:26.497
  -Wait, you think he thought
     it all out like that?
             -Yeah.

24:26.999 --> 24:28.599
          He wanted me
      to be just like him.

24:28.601 --> 24:30.501
         On the company
     and all that bullshit.

24:35.641 --> 24:37.241
      He was a sick fuck.

24:49.956 --> 24:51.722
Honey, you are nothing like him.

25:05.571 --> 25:07.771
       [heavy breathing]

25:56.556 --> 25:58.055
   You ready to get married?

25:59.659 --> 26:01.025
             Today?

26:01.027 --> 26:02.660
          Yes, today.

26:05.998 --> 26:08.132
          But I don't
     have anything to wear.

26:08.134 --> 26:09.700
             Oh...

26:09.702 --> 26:11.669
     I know just the place
       we could fix that.

26:15.808 --> 26:17.341
        [Roger giggling]

26:17.343 --> 26:19.977
         [somber music]

26:32.658 --> 26:33.841
         [Roger] Ready?

26:33.842 --> 26:35.025
             -Yeah.
    -Well, come on, show me.

26:53.079 --> 26:54.678
       You look perfect.

26:56.082 --> 26:57.081
            Thanks.

27:03.289 --> 27:04.822
        [Roger laughing]

27:19.905 --> 27:21.305
        [Roger whistles]

27:21.307 --> 27:22.806
          [door bangs]

27:27.713 --> 27:30.047
      God, are you there?
        It's me, Roger.

27:30.049 --> 27:31.749
           -[whacks]
              -Ow.

27:31.751 --> 27:32.816
             Ha ha.

27:32.818 --> 27:34.218
        [Roger chuckles]

27:37.757 --> 27:40.024
         Well, I think
    I know why you're here.

27:40.426 --> 27:44.728
   -We're ready for business.
      -Well, you certainly
   get points for enthusiasm.

27:46.032 --> 27:47.364
 Well, when you know, you know.

27:48.234 --> 27:51.735
 Oh, love, it's just wonderful.

27:52.405 --> 27:54.271
 Can I please see your license?

27:54.273 --> 27:55.806
            License?

27:55.808 --> 27:57.207
         We're in love,
       that's not enough?

27:57.209 --> 27:58.976
      Sorry, it's the law.

27:59.679 --> 28:00.844
          No escaping.

28:01.280 --> 28:02.880
             Fuck.

28:02.882 --> 28:04.815
         -[Roger] Damn.
      -I, uh-- I'm sorry,

28:04.817 --> 28:06.116
        I just-- I, ah.

28:06.118 --> 28:07.918
      Three days, my dear,

28:10.289 --> 28:12.072
        and I'll be more
    than happy to marry you.

28:12.073 --> 28:13.856
       -Hey, Daph, Daph!
    come on, slow, hold on.
   -How could I be so stupid?

28:13.859 --> 28:16.960
  Hey, shh, shh. It'll happen,
     okay three days, hey.

28:16.962 --> 28:18.395
     Three days is nothing.

28:23.936 --> 28:25.369
        Three weeks ago
    we were sneaking around

28:25.371 --> 28:26.937
     like naughty teenagers

28:27.873 --> 28:31.275
     and now we are in this
   beautiful town, together,

28:32.211 --> 28:33.377
       with our own <i> casa.</i>

28:35.247 --> 28:37.081
Come on, let's do something fun.

28:39.285 --> 28:40.217
           Like what?

28:40.219 --> 28:42.219
      Well, I don't know.
        Something stupid

28:42.221 --> 28:44.755
  like bowling, or go-carts...

28:46.058 --> 28:47.357
          or Funland.

28:52.965 --> 28:55.766
         [somber music]

29:17.957 --> 29:19.056
          [Roger] Oh!

29:19.925 --> 29:21.325
 You're too-- this is not fair!

29:25.364 --> 29:26.897
      Didn't even make it
     all the way up there.

29:27.833 --> 29:28.966
      This is great, babe.

29:28.968 --> 29:29.900
              Yes.

29:31.937 --> 29:32.870
          [Roger] Yes!

29:37.443 --> 29:38.842
         I won! I won!

29:38.844 --> 29:40.277
         -[bell rings]
            -Sorry.

29:40.279 --> 29:42.079
       -Congratulations.
            -Thanks.

29:42.081 --> 29:44.314
    -You proud of yourself?
         -I'm so proud.

29:44.316 --> 29:46.416
      -[woman] Chad. Chad.
   -[Roger] What do you get?
  Look you get the little elf.

29:46.418 --> 29:48.152
     [woman] The skeet ball
       machine's broken,

29:48.154 --> 29:49.086
        can you fix it?

29:57.163 --> 29:58.162
              Hey.

29:59.532 --> 30:00.464
              Hey.

30:03.035 --> 30:06.303
     Um, Daphne this is...
        this is Susanna.

30:10.409 --> 30:11.375
          Nice dress.

30:13.245 --> 30:14.211
           Thanks...

30:14.880 --> 30:16.079
     we're getting married.

30:20.286 --> 30:21.218
              Wow.

30:22.221 --> 30:23.854
        Ah, you hungry?

30:23.856 --> 30:25.355
    Let's go get some grub.

30:25.357 --> 30:27.491
           -But we--
-No, come on. Come on, let's go.

30:30.863 --> 30:31.995
             Here.

30:34.233 --> 30:35.332
        A wedding gift.

30:38.838 --> 30:39.970
            Thanks.

30:46.979 --> 30:47.911
             What?

